Special handling re CUDA 11.0, "Support for Kepler 'sm_30' and 'sm_32' architecture based products is dropped", and CUDA 12.0, "Kepler architecture support is removed" (that is, sm_35, sm_37).

Preamble '.target sm_3': doesn't exist; still special-cased to 'sm_%target_as_arch0'.

RUN: rm -f %t*
RUN: sed -e 's|sm_30|sm_3|g' < %S/../bare-1.s > %t.bare-1.s
RUN: %target_as_local_cmd -v -o /dev/null %t.bare-1.s > %t.stdout 2> %t.stderr; r=$?; [ x"$r" = x1 ]
RUN: ! test -s %t.stdout
RUN: sed -e 's|sm_30|sm_3|g' < verbose_stderr-sm_30.golden > %t.stderr.golden
RUN: f=%t.stderr.golden && s=$( wc -c < "$f" ) && n=$(( s - 1 )) && cmp -n "$n" "$f" %t.stderr

